      <section eId="sec_CC-696">
        <num>CC 696</num>
        <heading>696.  Indemnity</heading>
        <subsection eId="CC-696__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The owner of an enclosed estate having a right of passage is bound to indemnify
the owner of the servient estate for any damage caused by the exercise of the right of passage.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-696__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The right to demand indemnity against the owner of the enclosed estate may
become barred by prescription. The accrual of prescription has no effect on the right of
passage.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=110890</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
